{
  "esm": "0.4.0",
  "metadata": {
    "name": "NEI2016MonthlyEmis",
    "description": "US EPA 2016 NEI CMAQ-formatted monthly DataLoader. Converts monthly gridded anthropogenic+biogenic emissions from the 12US1 12-km Lambert Conformal domain to mixing ratio source rates (1/s) for 69 species. Species-specific temporal scaling: CO (day-of-week\u00d7diurnal), FORM (diurnal), ISOP (isoprene diurnal), NO/NO2 (NOx day-of-week\u00d7NOx diurnal), others (none). The gt-p3ep(lookup) gap is resolved via datetime.hour+floor+interp.linear for diurnal/day-of-week and table_lookup for the 94\u00d749 delp_dry_surface field. Migrated from EarthSciData.jl src/nei2016monthly.jl:358 (esm-ftdf).",
    "tags": [
      "emissions",
      "nei2016",
      "cmaq",
      "12us1",
      "anthropogenic",
      "biogenic",
      "dataloader",
      "monthly",
      "diurnal",
      "dayofweek",
      "surface_emissions"
    ],
    "created": "2026-05-30T00:00:00Z",
    "authors": [
      "EarthSciData.jl contributors",
      "EarthSciModels migration (esm-ftdf)"
    ],
    "references": [
      {
        "citation": "US EPA (2020). 2016 National Emissions Inventory v1. https://gaftp.epa.gov/Air/emismod/2016/"
      },
      {
        "citation": "Byun & Schere (2006). Models-3 CMAQ Modeling System. Applied Mechanics Reviews 59(2):51-77. \u2014 CMAQ IOAPI format."
      },
      {
        "citation": "Source: EarthSciData.jl/src/nei2016monthly.jl (see EarthSciModels docs/migration-tracker.md for pinned SHA). NEI2016MonthlyEmis DataLoader \u2014 69 algebraic observed variables with temporal scaling and flux-to-mixing-ratio conversion."
      }
    ]
  },
